news.title: Australia's property market stabilizes in February amid rate cut : CoreLogic data
news.para: Figures from property consultant CoreLogic showed prices across the nation rose 0.3% in February from January, ending three months of declines or no growth

news.title: Zuari Infraworld & Gangothri Developers to develop housing project in Hyderabad at Rs 1,500 crore
news.para: Spanning across 9.4 acres, this upscale development is being executed by Gangothri Group, with Zuari Infraworld serving as a development manager.

news.title: China's second-hand home prices fell by 0.4% in February: Report
news.para: Prices of second hand homes fell 7.3% year-on-year on average in February, the report said, while the average price of new builds in the same 100 cities increased by 2.7%.

news.title: Cement sector to grow 6-7% in 2025-26: Report
news.para: Most companies (21 out of 25) saw a yearon-year decline in EBITDA margins, but higher operating leverage and lower input costs improved margins quarter-overquarter.

news.title: Madhya Pradesh HC warns Bhopal collector over RERA order non-compliance
news.para: Verma said the RERA had issued RRC against the builder concerned in 2020 and asked the Bhopal collector to execute the order for recovery.

news.title: Trichy civic body targets top property tax defaulters
news.para: While 77% of the total property tax demand of Rs137.3 crore has been collected, arrears recovery remains sluggish, with only 38% of the Rs51.6 crore pending tax recovered as of March 2.

news.title: Pune: Residents of merged areas seek Rs 1,000 crore for development
news.para: The Pune Municipal Corporation (PMC) budget is expected to be presented on March 4. The organisation has written a letter to the civic body demanding funds.

news.title: Nashik civic body collects 33% more property tax between April and Feb 2024
news.para: With just one more month left for the current FY to come to an end, NMC has to collect property tax worth Rs16 crore more to reach its target of Rs250 crore.

news.title: Fresh bid to revive hybrid IT park project in Porvorim
news.para: ​Through the Goa Information Technology Development Corporation (GITDC), the department wants to ink a concessionaire agreement to operate the hybrid IT park on a Build Lease Operate Transfer (BLOT) model.

news.title: DDA generates Rs 5,185 crore from selling over 15,000 flats in two years
news.para: In the financial year 2024-25, DDA sold 7,184 flats, the majority under the first-come, first-served scheme, which offered discounted rates for construction workers, women, and people from SC/ST categories. Narela alone accounted for 2,700 flat sales in this period.

news.title: Panel formed to oversee lift registrations in societies in Noida
news.para: The panel will coordinate with the district administration and Noida Authority to ensure registrations, inspections, and compliance across 15 societies.

news.title: Bengaluru civic body collects 88% of Rs 5,210 crore property tax target in FY25
news.para: "We're auctioning properties that have defaulted on property tax payment and issuing notices in this regard," BBMP special commissioner (revenue) Munish Moudgil told TOI.

news.title: Odisha's H&UD department draws plan for streamlining affordable housing allotment
news.para: As per the task assigned, BDA was asked to take up more affordable housing projects based on requirements and hand them over to BMC for allotment purposes.

news.title: Ahmedabad: CID arrests Popular Builders' owner in decades-old land scam case
news.para: The case stems from a complaint filed by Kanu Thakor in Aug 2024, alleging that Patel, along with seven others, illegally acquired his ancestral land in Makarba in the city by forging documents.

news.title: Ludhiana development body evicts illegal occupiers of three LIG flats in sector-40
news.para: The officials said Glada had built 319 low-income group flats in Sector 40, of which 82 were occupied illegally.

news.title: Kerala: SIT seeks halting of resurvey of puramboke land
news.para: The SIT led by inspector general of police K Sethuraman, constituted as per a high court directive, has submitted a 741-page report to the govt.

news.title: Jaipur: Rampant constructions poses threat to Walled City legacy
news.para: "The regulation stipulates that any construction or modification facing main bazars shall endeavour to maintain the existing architectural volume and character.

news.title: Kolkata HC directs Darjeeling municipality to halt illegal construction on Mall Road
news.para: The municipality clarified that the beautification work and shifting of the hawkers down the extended road is being done by them, and funds are being provided by GTA.

news.title: Permission from police not needed for carrying out construction: Delhi government
news.para: "There is no provision under Delhi Municipal Corporation Act, 1957 by which a person is required to seek permission from police for carrying out construction," the circular read

news.title: Delhi government mandates all high-rise buildings to install anti-smog guns
news.para: Rising pollution was a major election issue in Delhi and the BJP had accused the previous AAP government of failing to check it.
